premise_source_doc_sentence: Like citalopram and escitalopram , didesmethyl  (  es  )  citalopram functions as a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor  (  SSRI  )  , and is responsible for some of its parents ' therapeutic benefits .
Like citalopram and escitalopram , desmethylcitalopram functions as a selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor  (  SSRI  )  , and is responsible for some of its parents ' therapeutic benefits .

It is based on the observation that the R isomer of citalopram can decrease the potency and inhibit the effects of the S isomer , probably through an allosteric interaction between two distinct , non-overlapping binding sites for the two different isomers on the serotonin transporter .
Whether escitalopram exhibits superior therapeutic properties to citalopram or merely represents an example of `` evergreening '' is controversial .
Escitalopram is the  (  S  )  - stereoisomer  (  Left-enantiomer  )  of the earlier Lundbeck drug citalopram , hence the name escitalopram .
